1
00:00:22,580 --> 00:00:27,660
♪Don't be afraid of the long journey♪

2
00:00:29,780 --> 00:00:34,740
♪Love will comfort your missing♪

3
00:00:34,900 --> 00:00:38,620
♪All the wounds will scab over♪

4
00:00:38,740 --> 00:00:41,980
♪And turn into the blossoms of time♪

5
00:00:41,980 --> 00:00:48,700
♪Someone will wipe them away for you♪

6
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:52,580
♪Don't feel lonely, moving on♪

7
00:00:52,940 --> 00:00:56,420
♪Share your story with time♪

8
00:00:56,460 --> 00:01:03,100
♪It will respond
with a gentle beam of light♪

9
00:01:03,220 --> 00:01:06,820
♪Wishing you find her in the crowd♪

10
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:10,220
♪And rest content with a simple life♪

11
00:01:10,380 --> 00:01:16,660
♪Even though life is full of regrets♪

12
00:01:17,380 --> 00:01:20,180
♪May you always maintain enthusiasm♪

13
00:01:20,220 --> 00:01:22,540
♪For every winter and summer♪

14
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:25,980
[Love Is Panacea]
[Episode 5]

15
00:01:25,980 --> 00:01:26,760
[The show is the Major Project
for Supporting Literature and Art]

16
00:01:26,760 --> 00:01:27,980
[in Sichuan Province in 2022]

17
00:01:27,980 --> 00:01:29,980
[Based on the novel "Healer"
by Ningmeng Yuyan]

18
00:01:55,420 --> 00:01:56,740
Hurry, something's happening.

19
00:01:59,020 --> 00:02:00,660
General Kouyate is here!

20
00:02:00,660 --> 00:02:01,980
He's got a team of armed soldiers.

21
00:02:06,540 --> 00:02:08,860
What's the point?
Just two cases of alcohol?

22
00:02:56,540 --> 00:02:57,500
Let's talk to the General.

23
00:02:58,820 --> 00:02:59,540
General!

24
00:02:59,780 --> 00:03:01,860
I lost the alcohol. I'll pay for it.

25
00:03:02,420 --> 00:03:03,420
Please don't cause trouble
in the hospital.

26
00:03:03,740 --> 00:03:05,300
What are you doing?

27
00:03:05,420 --> 00:03:07,420
I'll take the responsibility
for my fault.

28
00:03:08,460 --> 00:03:09,420
Little girl,

29
00:03:09,980 --> 00:03:11,500
you've picked a good place

30
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:12,740
to hide.

31
00:03:15,420 --> 00:03:16,420
General.

32
00:03:17,420 --> 00:03:18,180
You can speak Chinese?

33
00:03:18,420 --> 00:03:21,420
The General attended military school
in Shijiazhuang before.

34
00:03:21,900 --> 00:03:22,900
He even knows the local dialect.

35
00:03:24,260 --> 00:03:25,020
You bad girl!

36
00:03:25,060 --> 00:03:27,540
Do you know the consequences
of selling me fake alcohol?

37
00:03:27,620 --> 00:03:28,620
Fake alcohol?

38
00:03:29,420 --> 00:03:30,020
That's impossible.

39
00:03:30,020 --> 00:03:31,100
I never sell fake alcohol.

40
00:03:32,180 --> 00:03:34,620
Maybe you switched the alcohol yourself

41
00:03:34,660 --> 00:03:36,660
and purposely claimed it was fake.

42
00:03:36,860 --> 00:03:38,820
As an honorable General,

43
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:41,780
is it necessary for me to frame you?

44
00:03:43,140 --> 00:03:44,140
You arrogant girl,

45
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:46,420
let's settle our account later.

46
00:03:47,780 --> 00:03:49,540
I'm not here for you

47
00:03:50,220 --> 00:03:51,100
but for him.

48
00:03:52,180 --> 00:03:53,140
Wait, General,

49
00:03:53,420 --> 00:03:54,860
you already had the examination done.

50
00:03:55,420 --> 00:03:56,820
No tumors, no bleeding spots.

51
00:03:56,820 --> 00:03:58,420
How can you prove that you're sick?

52
00:03:59,420 --> 00:04:00,900
My instincts are never wrong.

53
00:04:01,180 --> 00:04:02,420
It's up to him to prove it.

54
00:04:03,140 --> 00:04:04,140
General,

55
00:04:05,140 --> 00:04:07,420
why are you so convinced
that you're sick?

56
00:04:11,220 --> 00:04:11,980
In the past,

57
00:04:13,540 --> 00:04:15,020
standing here,

58
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:16,500
I could shoot you in the head

59
00:04:17,140 --> 00:04:19,260
while you were standing downstairs.

60
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:20,740
But now I can't.

61
00:04:21,020 --> 00:04:22,860
It might be due to your vision decline

62
00:04:22,860 --> 00:04:24,140
or simply because you're getting old.

63
00:04:25,820 --> 00:04:28,020
In any case, you should
consult your attending doctor.

64
00:04:31,780 --> 00:04:34,180
[Eliot]

65
00:04:34,540 --> 00:04:35,540
Eliot?

66
00:04:38,420 --> 00:04:39,420
I'm not afraid of death.

67
00:04:40,260 --> 00:04:41,260
What I fear is dying

68
00:04:41,260 --> 00:04:43,420
without knowing who my enemies are.

69
00:04:44,220 --> 00:04:45,340
Eliot has got no guts.

70
00:04:45,980 --> 00:04:46,700
What about you?

71
00:04:52,660 --> 00:04:53,460
If you don't help me

72
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:55,060
figure out what's wrong with my brain,

73
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:56,460
I will kill her.

74
00:04:58,420 --> 00:05:00,900
Selling fake alcohol
is a serious crime in Lacaya,

75
00:05:01,820 --> 00:05:02,860
and now I suspect

76
00:05:02,860 --> 00:05:04,740
that it's her fake alcohol
causing my headaches.

77
00:05:04,820 --> 00:05:06,020
I didn't sell fake alcohol.

78
00:05:09,420 --> 00:05:10,420
Put your gun down.

79
00:05:10,740 --> 00:05:12,020
I can perform surgery for you,

80
00:05:12,180 --> 00:05:13,740
but can you trust me

81
00:05:13,820 --> 00:05:16,020
with your life?

82
00:05:25,420 --> 00:05:27,340
I'm not afraid of bullets.

83
00:05:28,140 --> 00:05:29,740
Not to mention a scalpel.

84
00:05:30,820 --> 00:05:31,500
Of course,

85
00:05:33,460 --> 00:05:34,420
if you dare

86
00:05:34,860 --> 00:05:36,180
to make any move,

87
00:05:36,180 --> 00:05:38,340
don't expect
to leave the operating table alive.

88
00:05:44,780 --> 00:05:45,420
Fine.

89
00:05:46,860 --> 00:05:48,860
I'll perform the surgery
for you in a month.

90
00:05:50,580 --> 00:05:51,580
I will

91
00:05:52,780 --> 00:05:54,420
definitely find your enemy.

92
00:05:58,100 --> 00:05:59,740
Good. I got the right guy.

93
00:06:01,300 --> 00:06:02,420
You're a good doctor.

94
00:06:08,180 --> 00:06:08,780
Are you all right?

95
00:06:08,940 --> 00:06:09,420
Yeah, I'm fine.

96
00:06:12,420 --> 00:06:13,460
Why did you agree with him?

97
00:06:14,260 --> 00:06:15,860
The hospital has already examined him,

98
00:06:16,140 --> 00:06:17,940
and the medical records clearly state

99
00:06:18,260 --> 00:06:19,420
that there's nothing wrong with him.

100
00:06:24,980 --> 00:06:26,180
Or

101
00:06:26,740 --> 00:06:27,700
did you agree to him

102
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:29,220
just to dispel his suspicions?

103
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:33,740
It's not because the general threatened

104
00:06:33,740 --> 00:06:34,860
that if you don't do it,

105
00:06:35,220 --> 00:06:36,860
he's going to kill me, right?

106
00:06:40,860 --> 00:06:42,500
You can't be that foolish, right?

107
00:06:43,260 --> 00:06:45,140
I can buy a ticket and leave the country
or go to another country,

108
00:06:45,140 --> 00:06:46,340
and then he can do nothing to me.

109
00:06:50,860 --> 00:06:51,860
Dr. Gu.

110
00:06:52,180 --> 00:06:53,260
What will you do

111
00:06:53,260 --> 00:06:54,420
if, after the surgery,

112
00:06:54,460 --> 00:06:55,420
you still can't find anything?

113
00:06:57,900 --> 00:06:59,220
It will be considered

114
00:06:59,420 --> 00:07:01,420
a major medical accident,

115
00:07:03,420 --> 00:07:05,420
and you might not even work
as a doctor anymore.

116
00:07:09,820 --> 00:07:11,060
You can't take such a risk.

117
00:07:18,420 --> 00:07:19,420
Su Wei'an.

118
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:22,700
You're really worried about me, huh?

119
00:07:26,420 --> 00:07:27,420
Absolutely not.

120
00:07:29,340 --> 00:07:30,140
I...

121
00:07:31,140 --> 00:07:32,420
I'm just worried
about getting involved in trouble.

122
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:34,740
If the surgery fails,

123
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:36,940
I won't be able to get away
as an interpreter.

124
00:07:43,740 --> 00:07:44,460
Wait. Why do you

125
00:07:44,460 --> 00:07:45,820
have to do this surgery?

126
00:07:48,140 --> 00:07:49,220
Because someone will die
if I don't do it.

127
00:07:51,860 --> 00:07:54,420
Do you know
what's wrong with the General?

128
00:07:57,660 --> 00:07:58,540
I mean,

129
00:07:58,540 --> 00:08:00,700
I'll die if I don't do it.

130
00:08:02,420 --> 00:08:02,980
Do you think

131
00:08:03,420 --> 00:08:05,060
we would have been able
to leave this room

132
00:08:05,060 --> 00:08:06,420
if I hadn't agreed

133
00:08:06,420 --> 00:08:08,580
to perform the surgery for him?

134
00:08:12,420 --> 00:08:13,220
Either way.

135
00:08:13,860 --> 00:08:15,420
Why don't you buy a ticket
back to China?

136
00:08:15,740 --> 00:08:16,780
I'll help you stall for time.

137
00:08:17,660 --> 00:08:19,580
The General can't go back to China.

138
00:08:24,140 --> 00:08:24,820
Su Wei'an.

139
00:08:25,820 --> 00:08:27,100
You don't trust me?

140
00:08:31,140 --> 00:08:32,140
I trust science.

141
00:08:33,420 --> 00:08:34,300
The CT scan

142
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:35,180
and MRI

143
00:08:35,180 --> 00:08:36,420
have both confirmed
that there's nothing wrong.

144
00:08:40,900 --> 00:08:42,900
General Kouyate is not sick!

145
00:08:45,060 --> 00:08:45,860
You are...

146
00:08:47,420 --> 00:08:48,220
Eliot.

147
00:08:48,620 --> 00:08:50,300
General Kouyate's attending doctor.

148
00:08:50,540 --> 00:08:51,420
Eliot.

149
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:53,420
You know Chinese?

150
00:08:53,540 --> 00:08:55,220
My grandmother is from Beijing.

151
00:08:55,700 --> 00:08:57,060
I learned a little from her.

152
00:08:58,260 --> 00:08:59,420
I've heard about you.

153
00:08:59,940 --> 00:09:01,900
Dr. Gu Yunzheng from Huaren Hospital.

154
00:09:02,420 --> 00:09:04,420
You don't want the record
of zero-table fatality rate?

155
00:09:05,900 --> 00:09:07,900
Zero table fatality rate.

156
00:09:09,060 --> 00:09:10,460
What a proud record!

157
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:13,900
It shows that Dr. Gu is still too young

158
00:09:14,260 --> 00:09:15,460
and has performed too few surgeries.

159
00:09:16,420 --> 00:09:19,020
Newcomers are always eager
to prove themselves.

160
00:09:19,140 --> 00:09:21,140
I can understand that, Dr. Gu.

161
00:09:21,740 --> 00:09:22,740
But remember,
patients are not just tools

162
00:09:23,420 --> 00:09:25,420
for doctors to gain fame and fortune.

163
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:26,700
You're talking nonsense!

164
00:09:27,820 --> 00:09:28,820
In China, Dr. Gu's

165
00:09:28,820 --> 00:09:30,420
weekly number
of outpatient visits and surgeries

166
00:09:30,980 --> 00:09:32,860
is dozens of times more
than your French doctors'.

167
00:09:33,420 --> 00:09:34,700
In terms of clinical experience,

168
00:09:35,020 --> 00:09:36,260
you're not necessarily better than him.

169
00:09:36,660 --> 00:09:37,420
Is that so?

170
00:09:38,220 --> 00:09:40,460
How does a patient like you know
about clinical experience?

171
00:09:45,420 --> 00:09:47,900
General Kouyate
has always been my patient.

172
00:09:48,180 --> 00:09:50,420
The diagnosis was the result
of a remote consultation

173
00:09:50,420 --> 00:09:52,060
with a French team of experts.

174
00:09:52,420 --> 00:09:53,060
May I ask,

175
00:09:53,060 --> 00:09:55,820
under the diagnosis result
of no mass found,

176
00:09:56,060 --> 00:09:58,180
why does Dr. Gu insist
on performing this surgery?

177
00:09:58,180 --> 00:09:58,900
Is it a provocation

178
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:00,740
against the French National Hospital?

179
00:10:00,860 --> 00:10:01,860
Dr. Eliot.

180
00:10:03,060 --> 00:10:04,060
Your hospital

181
00:10:04,860 --> 00:10:06,420
is not that important to me.

182
00:10:07,340 --> 00:10:08,980
I just want to provide

183
00:10:08,980 --> 00:10:10,420
the best medical treatment
for this patient.

184
00:10:11,420 --> 00:10:12,140
And now,

185
00:10:13,220 --> 00:10:15,180
I'm the patient's attending doctor.

186
00:10:27,010 --> 00:10:29,420
If you insist on performing the surgery,

187
00:10:31,420 --> 00:10:34,220
I'll invite experts
from the Lacaya Health Commission

188
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:35,300
to supervise the whole process.

189
00:10:35,300 --> 00:10:36,780
Dr. Gu, I'm warning you:

190
00:10:36,860 --> 00:10:37,900
if it's proven after the surgery

191
00:10:37,900 --> 00:10:39,820
that you've performed a fake surgery,

192
00:10:40,420 --> 00:10:41,660
I'll sue you

193
00:10:41,660 --> 00:10:43,420
until you never get a chance
to pick up a scalpel anymore.

194
00:10:49,140 --> 00:10:50,580
Miss Aggressive.

195
00:10:50,860 --> 00:10:52,420
I hope you won't regret it.

196
00:11:02,900 --> 00:11:03,940
Damn poker face.

197
00:11:04,420 --> 00:11:06,100
He's arrogant with his nose in the air.

198
00:11:12,420 --> 00:11:13,620
Stop looking.

199
00:11:13,620 --> 00:11:14,420
He's gone.

200
00:11:15,060 --> 00:11:16,060
He's so handsome.

201
00:11:16,940 --> 00:11:18,780
Handsome as a Roman statue.

202
00:11:21,220 --> 00:11:22,220
What's the use of being handsome?

203
00:11:22,780 --> 00:11:24,420
The patient has switched to our boss.

204
00:11:27,220 --> 00:11:28,220
Do you know him?

205
00:11:30,260 --> 00:11:32,180
He is General Kouyate's
attending doctor.

206
00:11:32,420 --> 00:11:33,420
I've asked around.

207
00:11:34,140 --> 00:11:36,900
He's the head of the Neurosurgery
Department at the French National Hospital

208
00:11:37,740 --> 00:11:40,060
and also a professor of neurosurgery
at the University of Paris VI.

209
00:11:40,980 --> 00:11:44,060
He can be considered
an authority in neurosurgery.

210
00:11:45,140 --> 00:11:46,140
Authority?

211
00:11:48,780 --> 00:11:50,980
So, who is better, him or Dr. Gu?

212
00:11:53,060 --> 00:11:54,460
Well, that's hard to say.

213
00:11:56,340 --> 00:11:57,340
The University of Paris VI

214
00:11:57,420 --> 00:12:00,420
is the largest scientific
and medical institution in France

215
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:03,820
and one of the top five
research universities in the world.

216
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:08,460
Since this authority said
that General Kouyate is not sick.

217
00:12:08,660 --> 00:12:10,340
Why does he insist
on finding the problem?

218
00:12:13,420 --> 00:12:15,420
I also hope the boss finds a reason
to say no.

219
00:12:16,100 --> 00:12:17,420
Those men are armed and dangerous.

220
00:12:18,420 --> 00:12:19,460
They're not to be trifled with.

221
00:12:19,460 --> 00:12:20,900
What if the treatment fails?

222
00:12:21,420 --> 00:12:22,420
Bullets don't discriminate.

223
00:12:24,180 --> 00:12:25,180
Then what should we do?

224
00:12:25,580 --> 00:12:27,380
Has Dr. Gu changed his mind?

225
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:33,160
[Doctor's Office]

226
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:35,900
What are you doing?

227
00:12:37,580 --> 00:12:39,260
Join the fight
if my objections are overruled.

228
00:12:39,660 --> 00:12:40,660
Search for references

229
00:12:41,140 --> 00:12:42,260
to guard

230
00:12:42,260 --> 00:12:44,100
the zero mortality on the operating table
for our boss.

231
00:12:45,740 --> 00:12:47,900
Zero mortality on the operating table?

232
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:50,660
Is it a competition and

233
00:12:51,340 --> 00:12:52,340
impressive?

234
00:12:54,140 --> 00:12:56,700
Maybe it's a competition with oneself.

235
00:12:57,420 --> 00:12:58,500
Which doctor

236
00:12:58,500 --> 00:13:00,780
wouldn't want a zero mortality
on their operating table?

237
00:13:01,180 --> 00:13:02,180
What about you?

238
00:13:04,180 --> 00:13:04,980
Me?

239
00:13:06,220 --> 00:13:07,100
I don't have a record.

240
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:09,420
Help me find it.

241
00:13:10,020 --> 00:13:10,780
I'm running out of time.

242
00:13:10,780 --> 00:13:12,260
I have to finish reading all
of this tonight.

243
00:13:14,420 --> 00:13:15,420
This is...

244
00:13:16,820 --> 00:13:17,700
So much.

245
00:13:17,780 --> 00:13:20,140
How long will it take
for both of us to finish?

246
00:13:20,420 --> 00:13:21,460
Maybe an all-nighter

247
00:13:22,740 --> 00:13:24,660
would be enough for the two of us.

248
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:25,740
An all-nighter?

249
00:13:26,300 --> 00:13:26,980
No way!

250
00:13:27,420 --> 00:13:28,740
Staying up all night will give me acne.

251
00:13:30,220 --> 00:13:31,420
Fine.

252
00:13:38,420 --> 00:13:39,420
Let's just do it.

253
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:43,620
Tell me.

254
00:13:44,100 --> 00:13:45,100
What am I going to do?

255
00:13:51,780 --> 00:13:53,020
Can you read

256
00:13:53,220 --> 00:13:54,060
the surgical records?

257
00:13:54,740 --> 00:13:55,580
What should I focus on?

258
00:13:55,940 --> 00:13:56,820
Well...

259
00:13:59,780 --> 00:14:00,500
Never mind.

260
00:14:04,660 --> 00:14:06,660
Can you understand

261
00:14:06,660 --> 00:14:07,980
the shadows and masses
in this CT scan image?

262
00:14:19,820 --> 00:14:21,420
Am I useless?

263
00:14:22,900 --> 00:14:23,940
Of course not.

264
00:14:24,660 --> 00:14:25,700
You're very helpful to me.

265
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:28,420
Help me

266
00:14:29,540 --> 00:14:31,100
sort these

267
00:14:31,100 --> 00:14:32,420
abstracts of the papers.

268
00:14:33,140 --> 00:14:34,460
I'll tell you how to do it.

269
00:14:36,180 --> 00:14:37,140
Take this one for example.

270
00:14:38,380 --> 00:14:40,100
Put it together with others

271
00:14:40,580 --> 00:14:41,740
that are the same,

272
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:43,460
and put them over here,

273
00:14:44,420 --> 00:14:45,420
and then this one...

274
00:14:55,340 --> 00:14:59,340
[Medical Records Report, Name: Kouyate]

275
00:15:01,420 --> 00:15:03,380
[Du Yongsong]

276
00:15:15,780 --> 00:15:16,420
What's up?

277
00:15:16,820 --> 00:15:18,420
Why did you agree
to perform surgery on a patient

278
00:15:18,580 --> 00:15:20,420
without knowing the lesion?

279
00:15:21,900 --> 00:15:22,660
You got it?

280
00:15:22,780 --> 00:15:24,060
You can't perform this surgery.

281
00:15:24,060 --> 00:15:24,980
[Jinhai City]

282
00:15:24,980 --> 00:15:26,820
I've sent a letter
to Friendship Hospital.

283
00:15:27,020 --> 00:15:29,420
They'll talk to the patient
about canceling the surgery.

284
00:15:30,340 --> 00:15:32,420
In what capacity are you ordering me?

285
00:15:33,980 --> 00:15:34,740
The director?

286
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:36,980
Or my father?

287
00:15:37,180 --> 00:15:38,540
No matter whatever capacity I am,

288
00:15:38,540 --> 00:15:39,420
I'm doing this for your own good.

289
00:15:40,180 --> 00:15:41,820
That patient is a local dignitary.

290
00:15:42,420 --> 00:15:43,900
What if something goes wrong
during your surgery?

291
00:15:43,980 --> 00:15:44,780
Huh?

292
00:15:44,780 --> 00:15:46,420
Do you want to end up like your mother?

293
00:15:49,420 --> 00:15:50,420
You don't deserve to talk about her.

294
00:15:53,700 --> 00:15:54,740
I'll tell you again.

295
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:56,180
Listen to me carefully.

296
00:15:57,060 --> 00:15:59,100
She abandoned us first.

297
00:16:01,700 --> 00:16:03,420
You abandoned her first.

298
00:16:25,980 --> 00:16:27,300
Every day, we encounter

299
00:16:27,300 --> 00:16:28,620
various diseases,

300
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:30,980
and as a doctor,

301
00:16:31,220 --> 00:16:33,260
the most painful thing is
to feel helpless

302
00:16:33,580 --> 00:16:35,340
in the face of these diseases.

303
00:16:35,900 --> 00:16:37,700
So, I hope all of you here,
my fellow students,

304
00:16:37,980 --> 00:16:40,660
never get used to this kind of pain

305
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:43,300
and never give up easily.

306
00:16:44,260 --> 00:16:45,300
Thank you.

307
00:16:46,660 --> 00:16:47,420
Okay.

308
00:16:47,700 --> 00:16:48,980
That's it for this class, dismissed.

309
00:17:03,460 --> 00:17:04,260
Wei'an.

310
00:17:06,740 --> 00:17:07,660
Su Wei'an.

311
00:17:08,100 --> 00:17:09,100
What's wrong?

312
00:17:10,100 --> 00:17:11,100
Do you like Mr. Gu?

313
00:17:12,340 --> 00:17:13,300
No.

314
00:17:13,980 --> 00:17:15,140
Don't joke about it.

315
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:16,620
No?

316
00:17:16,940 --> 00:17:18,340
You're acting so smitten.

317
00:17:18,980 --> 00:17:21,380
No wonder you kept asking questions
in class today.

318
00:17:21,820 --> 00:17:23,780
Were you trying
to get Mr. Gu's attention?

319
00:17:23,860 --> 00:17:24,580
No.

320
00:17:25,220 --> 00:17:26,700
When did you start liking him?

321
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:29,700
The time he helped you out
during the final exam when you were late,

322
00:17:29,980 --> 00:17:30,980
you've been in love
with him since then, right?

323
00:17:36,140 --> 00:17:37,220
I don't like him.

324
00:17:38,340 --> 00:17:39,980
I wanted to be him.

325
00:17:50,980 --> 00:17:51,980
General.

326
00:17:52,660 --> 00:17:53,820
I advise you to think twice.

327
00:17:53,820 --> 00:17:54,940
You can't joke with your life.

328
00:17:54,940 --> 00:17:55,740
General!

329
00:17:55,740 --> 00:17:57,300
Miss, you can't go in.

330
00:18:02,980 --> 00:18:03,740
[Guizhou Moutai]
General.

331
00:18:04,020 --> 00:18:05,020
Two cases of Moutai.

332
00:18:05,980 --> 00:18:06,940
Double compensation.

333
00:18:07,460 --> 00:18:08,100
Is that enough?

334
00:18:09,140 --> 00:18:10,780
I can add more if it's not.

335
00:18:39,820 --> 00:18:40,940
This taste is spot on.

336
00:18:44,580 --> 00:18:46,020
Now, tell me,

337
00:18:49,260 --> 00:18:50,220
why you're here

338
00:18:50,980 --> 00:18:51,980
to visit me?

339
00:19:12,980 --> 00:19:13,980
General,

340
00:19:15,900 --> 00:19:16,900
please give up the surgery.

341
00:19:17,980 --> 00:19:18,980
Is Gu Yunzheng scared?

342
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:22,540
So he sent a woman to beg for mercy?

343
00:19:23,540 --> 00:19:25,540
No, he has no idea I'm here.

344
00:19:26,180 --> 00:19:29,460
General, there are many possibilities
for your abnormal condition.

345
00:19:29,780 --> 00:19:30,860
Surgery may not be necessary.

346
00:19:32,620 --> 00:19:33,420
General,

347
00:19:34,420 --> 00:19:35,980
Miss Su is right.

348
00:19:36,500 --> 00:19:38,580
I will accompany you
to the Paris Main Hospital next month.

349
00:19:38,980 --> 00:19:41,260
They have the most advanced equipment
in the world.

350
00:19:41,260 --> 00:19:42,260
We can try again there.

351
00:19:42,340 --> 00:19:43,300
Get away!

352
00:19:45,740 --> 00:19:46,580
It's been a year.

353
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:48,580
I know

354
00:19:48,580 --> 00:19:49,980
there's a time bomb inside me,

355
00:19:50,580 --> 00:19:51,980
but you just can't find it.

356
00:19:52,420 --> 00:19:53,980
So, should I just surrender?

357
00:19:55,380 --> 00:19:56,420
What does Gu Yunzheng say?

358
00:19:58,260 --> 00:20:00,980
He's not giving up, just like you.

359
00:20:02,980 --> 00:20:04,620
He said that in the face of disease,

360
00:20:05,660 --> 00:20:08,540
the doctor and the patient
should be on the same team.

361
00:20:14,740 --> 00:20:15,740
To Dr. Gu.

362
00:20:17,420 --> 00:20:19,540
You Chinese also say

363
00:20:19,860 --> 00:20:21,020
nothing ventured,

364
00:20:21,700 --> 00:20:23,140
nothing gained.

365
00:20:40,580 --> 00:20:42,020
General,

366
00:20:43,020 --> 00:20:46,980
what does it take for you
to give up the surgery?

367
00:20:46,980 --> 00:20:48,340
Miss Su,

368
00:20:48,340 --> 00:20:50,260
don't you want my surgery
to be successful?

369
00:20:50,780 --> 00:20:51,980
Eliminating the enemy

370
00:20:52,300 --> 00:20:53,620
and living a long and healthy life.

371
00:20:54,100 --> 00:20:55,420
I can drink more alcohol,

372
00:20:56,260 --> 00:20:57,580
and you can earn more money.

373
00:20:57,780 --> 00:20:59,620
I don't want money.

374
00:21:01,460 --> 00:21:03,980
I just want Dr. Gu to be safe.

375
00:21:05,980 --> 00:21:09,180
Are you the money-obsessed Miss Su?

376
00:21:16,340 --> 00:21:19,340
Dr. Gu is one

377
00:21:19,700 --> 00:21:23,380
of the best neurosurgeons in China.

378
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:26,980
Are you sure you want

379
00:21:27,220 --> 00:21:31,020
to ruin a doctor's career
for your stubbornness?

380
00:21:31,540 --> 00:21:34,380
If he really is
as excellent as you claim,

381
00:21:35,540 --> 00:21:37,460
why do you think he will lose?

382
00:21:40,580 --> 00:21:43,540
Because you're not really sick.

383
00:21:48,700 --> 00:21:50,980
Do you know that your condition

384
00:21:51,620 --> 00:21:53,970
is called hypochondria in psychology?

385
00:21:53,970 --> 00:21:54,370
Miss Su.

386
00:21:54,370 --> 00:21:56,660
You should seek psychological help,

387
00:21:56,660 --> 00:21:58,140
but not Dr. Gu.

388
00:21:59,370 --> 00:22:00,340
How dare you?

389
00:22:01,740 --> 00:22:02,930
Get her out of here.

390
00:22:02,970 --> 00:22:03,700
General.

391
00:22:04,450 --> 00:22:05,620
Let go of me.

392
00:22:05,700 --> 00:22:06,140
General.

393
00:22:06,410 --> 00:22:07,180
She's drunk.

394
00:22:07,180 --> 00:22:08,340
She didn't mean to offend you.

395
00:22:08,580 --> 00:22:09,930
Miss Su, please stop talking.

396
00:22:09,930 --> 00:22:10,930
I'll take you home.

397
00:22:11,370 --> 00:22:12,450
General!

398
00:22:13,970 --> 00:22:16,970
Tell Dr. Gu
to take this crazy woman back.

399
00:22:16,970 --> 00:22:17,970
Yes, sir.

400
00:22:33,060 --> 00:22:33,620
Hello?

401
00:22:34,740 --> 00:22:35,890
Come to the General's residence.

402
00:22:35,890 --> 00:22:37,580
And take the crazy woman away.

403
00:22:38,370 --> 00:22:39,260
She's drunk.

404
00:22:41,020 --> 00:22:41,980
Alright, I got it.

405
00:22:45,260 --> 00:22:46,580
That idiot.

406
00:22:51,780 --> 00:22:52,780
That Dr. Gu,

407
00:22:53,140 --> 00:22:54,220
who is he to you?

408
00:22:56,340 --> 00:22:57,060
He...

409
00:22:57,740 --> 00:22:59,740
he is my...

410
00:23:01,220 --> 00:23:02,100
Boyfriend?

411
00:23:03,700 --> 00:23:04,660
No.

412
00:23:11,700 --> 00:23:12,660
He's over there,

413
00:23:13,980 --> 00:23:14,980
and I'm here.

414
00:23:16,980 --> 00:23:19,460
He is my teacher,

415
00:23:20,980 --> 00:23:23,660
the person I admire the most,

416
00:23:27,660 --> 00:23:31,100
and the one I used to want to be.

417
00:23:31,220 --> 00:23:32,860
Why did you say "used to"?

418
00:23:33,540 --> 00:23:34,580
I...

419
00:23:34,980 --> 00:23:36,980
I didn't have such good luck.

420
00:23:37,820 --> 00:23:38,820
The way you are now

421
00:23:38,980 --> 00:23:40,700
reminds me of my mentor.

422
00:23:41,620 --> 00:23:43,500
She often sighed like this

423
00:23:44,820 --> 00:23:46,260
and complained to God.

424
00:23:46,980 --> 00:23:49,980
She loved playing dice in her lab.

425
00:23:50,100 --> 00:23:51,780
Did your mentor

426
00:23:52,220 --> 00:23:54,660
also have trouble with her experiments?

427
00:23:56,420 --> 00:23:58,100
Because she always chose

428
00:23:58,100 --> 00:23:59,780
the less traveled path.

429
00:24:01,420 --> 00:24:03,020
Though she often failed,

430
00:24:03,980 --> 00:24:06,980
Dr. Marta was still
the most amazing doctor

431
00:24:07,780 --> 00:24:08,820
I've ever known.

432
00:24:08,980 --> 00:24:10,340
Dr. Marta?

433
00:24:12,900 --> 00:24:13,980
The one

434
00:24:14,740 --> 00:24:17,100
who first attempted cell transplantation

435
00:24:17,100 --> 00:24:19,580
to treat Huntington's disease
in the world, right?

436
00:24:19,780 --> 00:24:20,780
How would you know?

437
00:24:22,780 --> 00:24:25,540
This was her experiment
on a rare disease over 20 years ago.

438
00:24:26,100 --> 00:24:28,620
You probably weren't even born yet.

439
00:24:36,260 --> 00:24:36,860
Su Wei'an.

440
00:24:48,100 --> 00:24:49,100
Thank you.

441
00:24:52,780 --> 00:24:53,780
Dr. Eliot.

442
00:24:54,180 --> 00:24:55,180
It's getting late.

443
00:24:55,620 --> 00:24:57,620
We should go back to the hospital. Bye.

444
00:24:58,620 --> 00:24:59,300
Dr. Gu.

445
00:25:01,940 --> 00:25:02,900
Dr. Gu.

446
00:25:03,260 --> 00:25:05,340
Why are you so determined
to perform this surgery?

447
00:25:07,820 --> 00:25:08,980
Because, as a doctor,

448
00:25:08,980 --> 00:25:10,940
we should never ignore any signal

449
00:25:10,940 --> 00:25:12,420
coming from the patient's body.

450
00:25:17,640 --> 00:25:21,260
[Friendship Hospital]

451
00:25:21,260 --> 00:25:22,460
Let's drink.

452
00:25:22,940 --> 00:25:25,620
Either you or I

453
00:25:26,340 --> 00:25:27,540
must get drunk.

454
00:25:29,500 --> 00:25:30,500
Enough!

455
00:25:47,300 --> 00:25:48,420
Why did you

456
00:25:48,980 --> 00:25:50,900
go to the General's house
to drink tonight?

457
00:25:51,620 --> 00:25:54,620
It's all because of you, causing trouble

458
00:25:56,180 --> 00:25:58,900
and giving me no peace of mind.

459
00:25:58,940 --> 00:26:00,620
Who is causing trouble here?

460
00:26:01,780 --> 00:26:02,340
It's midnight,

461
00:26:02,340 --> 00:26:04,260
and I had to go
to the General's house to pick you up.

462
00:26:06,300 --> 00:26:07,820
Eliot.

463
00:26:08,620 --> 00:26:12,620
Please help me plead with the General.

464
00:26:16,860 --> 00:26:17,860
Su Wei'an.

465
00:26:18,620 --> 00:26:20,740
Can you please stay away from Eliot?

466
00:26:20,740 --> 00:26:23,020
Why? He's a good person.

467
00:26:24,620 --> 00:26:26,220
Because you're my interpreter,

468
00:26:26,220 --> 00:26:27,620
not Eliot's.

469
00:26:28,780 --> 00:26:31,660
Tonight, just rest here

470
00:26:32,700 --> 00:26:34,300
and clear your head.

471
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:40,060
Don't leave.

472
00:27:26,780 --> 00:27:27,940
(These features)

473
00:27:28,300 --> 00:27:29,940
(are so)

474
00:27:30,220 --> 00:27:31,220
(ordinary.)

475
00:28:04,340 --> 00:28:05,340
Fang Mingfan.

476
00:28:05,940 --> 00:28:06,860
What are you trying to do?

477
00:28:08,100 --> 00:28:09,740
I didn't expect you to be like this.

478
00:28:10,180 --> 00:28:11,620
What am I like?

479
00:28:12,900 --> 00:28:13,780
Your face,

480
00:28:14,100 --> 00:28:14,780
wipe it off.

481
00:28:25,940 --> 00:28:26,940
Oh no!

482
00:28:28,220 --> 00:28:30,780
I didn't remove my makeup all night.
This is a disaster.

483
00:28:30,980 --> 00:28:32,820
Even a hundred face masks
won't make up for it.

484
00:28:35,460 --> 00:28:36,100
Paper.

485
00:28:47,820 --> 00:28:48,940
Fang Mingfan, I'm warning you,

486
00:28:49,100 --> 00:28:50,260
don't tell anyone.

487
00:28:51,820 --> 00:28:52,940
Tell anyone what?

488
00:28:55,500 --> 00:28:57,300
Don't tell anyone
that my makeup is ruined,

489
00:28:57,300 --> 00:28:58,460
as well as

490
00:28:58,460 --> 00:28:59,620
that I spent the night at your place.

491
00:29:01,100 --> 00:29:02,580
Who am I going to tell?

492
00:29:03,340 --> 00:29:04,220
Well...

493
00:29:06,660 --> 00:29:08,420
You can't tell anyone.

494
00:29:08,420 --> 00:29:09,300
Did you hear me?

495
00:29:09,300 --> 00:29:10,260
If you tell anyone,

496
00:29:10,260 --> 00:29:11,460
I won't spare you.

497
00:29:12,340 --> 00:29:12,780
Okay.

498
00:29:12,780 --> 00:29:13,620
Stop laughing.

499
00:29:15,500 --> 00:29:16,260
Jiang.

500
00:29:19,300 --> 00:29:20,940
You're pretty,

501
00:29:21,620 --> 00:29:22,620
even with your ruined makeup.

502
00:29:38,940 --> 00:29:39,940
So early?

503
00:29:46,300 --> 00:29:48,940
Why are you wearing yesterday's clothes?

504
00:29:52,860 --> 00:29:54,220
Aren't you, too?

505
00:29:54,500 --> 00:29:55,820
I woke up early in the morning

506
00:29:56,620 --> 00:29:57,620
and went for a workout.

507
00:29:59,460 --> 00:30:00,460
I...

508
00:30:01,420 --> 00:30:02,500
I went to make some money,

509
00:30:03,260 --> 00:30:04,420
talking business with a big client.

510
00:30:08,340 --> 00:30:09,300
You've been drinking.

511
00:30:09,420 --> 00:30:10,420
Who were you drinking with?

512
00:30:14,340 --> 00:30:16,480
[Friendship Hospital]

513
00:30:20,860 --> 00:30:22,260
Have you found the direction
for the surgery?

514
00:30:23,500 --> 00:30:24,500
Are you sober?

515
00:30:25,620 --> 00:30:26,620
No more headaches?

516
00:30:28,060 --> 00:30:28,700
Then let's go

517
00:30:29,300 --> 00:30:30,780
for breakfast.

518
00:30:31,300 --> 00:30:33,620
You still have the mood for breakfast?

519
00:30:34,780 --> 00:30:36,620
You've drunk heavily,

520
00:30:36,700 --> 00:30:38,300
why can't I eat?

521
00:30:38,820 --> 00:30:39,420
I...

522
00:30:39,420 --> 00:30:42,620
I know you did it for me.

523
00:30:44,760 --> 00:30:46,760
You didn't want
my reputation to be stained.

524
00:30:47,800 --> 00:30:48,760
But Su Wei'an,

525
00:30:49,720 --> 00:30:50,640
let me ask you something.

526
00:30:51,280 --> 00:30:51,920
Why do you think

527
00:30:52,600 --> 00:30:55,040
I gave General Kouyate

528
00:30:55,040 --> 00:30:56,360
the surgery?

529
00:30:56,720 --> 00:30:57,640
How do I know?

530
00:30:59,200 --> 00:31:02,120
Is it because the General put a gun
to you

531
00:31:02,200 --> 00:31:04,720
or because you wanted to compete

532
00:31:05,080 --> 00:31:05,880
with Eliot?

533
00:31:09,240 --> 00:31:09,920
Su Wei'an,

534
00:31:11,280 --> 00:31:12,600
I'm a doctor.

535
00:31:12,880 --> 00:31:15,600
I have only one reason
to give the surgery.

536
00:31:16,160 --> 00:31:18,480
The patient has surgical indications

537
00:31:18,760 --> 00:31:20,600
and needs the surgery.

538
00:31:20,920 --> 00:31:22,240
Why can't you believe me?

539
00:31:22,360 --> 00:31:23,320
I believe you.

540
00:31:25,160 --> 00:31:27,360
But I went through all the medical cases

541
00:31:27,360 --> 00:31:28,840
with unclear images,

542
00:31:29,880 --> 00:31:31,600
and none of them is similar
to the General's case.

543
00:31:32,160 --> 00:31:33,600
So, you gave up?

544
00:31:35,440 --> 00:31:37,440
Did Huaren Medical University
only teach you

545
00:31:38,560 --> 00:31:39,800
how you could give up?

546
00:31:44,840 --> 00:31:45,760
What?

547
00:31:45,760 --> 00:31:46,720
Silly girl, indeed.

548
00:31:47,400 --> 00:31:48,400
No wonder you're an undergrad.

549
00:31:48,960 --> 00:31:50,240
I'm not an undergrad.

550
00:31:51,360 --> 00:31:52,560
I have a bachelor's degree.

551
00:31:53,560 --> 00:31:54,600
Bachelor's degree?

552
00:31:57,280 --> 00:32:00,120
In college classes,

553
00:32:00,120 --> 00:32:01,680
Mr. Gu taught you something.

554
00:32:01,960 --> 00:32:03,720
But you forgot it all, I guess.

555
00:32:04,040 --> 00:32:05,160
I really don't know

556
00:32:05,160 --> 00:32:07,240
how you got your bachelor's degree.

557
00:32:09,080 --> 00:32:10,080
Everyone,

558
00:32:10,080 --> 00:32:11,160
today,

559
00:32:11,880 --> 00:32:14,280
we're going to learn
the diagnostic thinking of brain tumors

560
00:32:14,560 --> 00:32:17,240
combined with practice.

561
00:32:17,240 --> 00:32:18,480
It's very clear

562
00:32:18,480 --> 00:32:20,080
that we can't see obvious lesions

563
00:32:20,280 --> 00:32:22,280
from the patient's CT.

564
00:32:22,560 --> 00:32:24,560
Then, let's check the MRI.

565
00:32:24,560 --> 00:32:26,720
We can clearly see some lesions

566
00:32:26,720 --> 00:32:28,560
on the patient's brainstem, huh?

567
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:34,000
Mr. Gu,

568
00:32:34,160 --> 00:32:37,360
if lesions still can't be seen from MRI,

569
00:32:37,360 --> 00:32:38,560
what should the doctor do?

570
00:32:39,200 --> 00:32:41,200
He should do a clinical follow-up,

571
00:32:41,600 --> 00:32:44,080
judge, by experience,
the growth of the disease,

572
00:32:44,200 --> 00:32:46,160
and confirm the intervals of follow-ups.

573
00:32:46,400 --> 00:32:50,040
Then what must a doctor trust,

574
00:32:50,040 --> 00:32:51,560
clinical experience,
or precision instrument?

575
00:32:51,960 --> 00:32:53,280
When a doctor cures diseases,

576
00:32:54,560 --> 00:32:55,720
guidance is his criterion,

577
00:32:56,280 --> 00:32:57,480
knowledge is his base,

578
00:32:58,400 --> 00:33:00,040
and experience is his tool.

579
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:02,600
With rigorous examination results,

580
00:33:02,720 --> 00:33:03,560
the doctor can figure out

581
00:33:04,160 --> 00:33:06,080
detailed lesions quickly and precisely

582
00:33:06,880 --> 00:33:08,280
without delay or misdiagnosis.

583
00:33:09,040 --> 00:33:10,880
So, I want you guys to keep it in mind.

584
00:33:10,880 --> 00:33:12,400
Only by using the instruments

585
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:14,040
and developing
your own clinical thinking

586
00:33:14,320 --> 00:33:16,200
can you be
really responsible for patients.

587
00:33:17,480 --> 00:33:18,560
You remember me.

588
00:33:20,120 --> 00:33:23,200
So, you kept asking questions in class

589
00:33:23,400 --> 00:33:25,120
